                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14473389" author="fplass" created="Fri, 19 Oct 2012 04:00:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I assume that the problem is not limited to classes implmenting the &apos;Comparable&apos; interface but also affects other cases of generic methods defined by an implemented interface. However, due to the special treatment of comparison operations by the DefaultTypeTransformer the simple workaround (only applicable for self defined classes anyway) of using dynamic metaprogramming for implementing the &apos;compareTo()&apos; method and implementing the corresponding checks in a type checker plugin does not work. The only option would be to subclass &apos;StaticTypeCheckingVisitor&apos; and add extra checks for &apos;compareTo()&apos; method calls, which looks like a substantial effort for a workaround.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
